1
00:00:01,359 --> 00:00:02,488
I'm sorry.

2
00:00:02,859 --> 00:00:05,959
I should've paid more attention.

3
00:00:07,859 --> 00:00:09,028
I'm okay.

4
00:00:09,299 --> 00:00:12,499
When you get tired, you can just say so.

5
00:00:12,938 --> 00:00:14,769
No one will blame you for saying that.

6
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:17,938
Goodness, kiddo.

7
00:00:18,109 --> 00:00:20,738
You made such a huge first impression.

8
00:00:26,419 --> 00:00:27,518
Ha Na.

9
00:00:30,518 --> 00:00:33,889
Can you show your new friend around the children's home?

10
00:00:34,188 --> 00:00:35,819
- Sure. - Thank you.

11
00:00:36,758 --> 00:00:38,989
Reverent Mother, you have a guest.

12
00:00:39,158 --> 00:00:40,298
All right.

13
00:00:44,268 --> 00:00:45,929
Hi, my name is Lee Ha Na.

14
00:00:46,338 --> 00:00:47,639
What's your name?

15
00:00:49,139 --> 00:00:50,268
I don't know.

16
00:00:51,539 --> 00:00:53,239
Don't you have a name?

17
00:00:56,709 --> 00:00:58,349
Do you want to check out my hideout first?

18
00:01:08,189 --> 00:01:11,159
Gosh, it's so cool.

19
00:01:13,429 --> 00:01:15,028
This is your hideout?

20
00:01:15,599 --> 00:01:16,698
Yes.

21
00:01:17,498 --> 00:01:18,969
No one knows about it.

22
00:01:19,799 --> 00:01:21,138
Well, they don't come here even if they know.

23
00:01:21,898 --> 00:01:23,668
They don't know how cool it looks.

24
00:01:29,079 --> 00:01:30,409
You're cool.

25
00:01:32,049 --> 00:01:33,379
- Me? - Yes.

26
00:01:34,349 --> 00:01:37,489
It's really cool that you know a place like this.

27
00:01:37,888 --> 00:01:38,918
Don't mention it.

28
00:01:39,148 --> 00:01:40,918
It feels like the wind blows to comfort me...

29
00:01:40,918 --> 00:01:43,258
when I feel troubled at heart.

30
00:01:43,858 --> 00:01:47,799
It feels like the wind is patting my heart slowly.

31
00:01:49,498 --> 00:01:52,398
That's how a mom's hand must feel.

32
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:54,599
"Mom's hand?"

33
00:01:55,198 --> 00:01:57,269
I read in books and watched on TV...

34
00:01:57,409 --> 00:02:00,379
that a mom's hand feels warm, cozy,

35
00:02:00,379 --> 00:02:02,409
and gentle on you.

36
00:02:05,008 --> 00:02:06,819
What else is good about this place?

37
00:02:07,918 --> 00:02:09,849
When you sit here,

38
00:02:10,018 --> 00:02:12,589
you can be the first to see...

39
00:02:12,719 --> 00:02:14,219
who's coming and going.

40
00:02:14,958 --> 00:02:16,728
And who's coming for us, too.

41
00:02:17,928 --> 00:02:19,659
So, when I sit here,

42
00:02:19,928 --> 00:02:21,928
I don't feel alone even when I am.

43
00:02:25,029 --> 00:02:27,939
Hey! That's where we took a break, right?

44
00:02:28,198 --> 00:02:30,168
- Right? - Yes.

45
00:02:33,379 --> 00:02:34,539
Ha Na.

46
00:02:38,048 --> 00:02:41,619
She came after her previous adoption was terminated,

47
00:02:41,779 --> 00:02:43,349
so it wouldn't be easy to bring it up to her.

48
00:02:43,849 --> 00:02:45,789
She has been abused,

49
00:02:46,349 --> 00:02:48,018
so she could feel wary of people.

50
00:02:49,119 --> 00:02:51,089
We should've looked for her a little earlier.

51
00:02:51,888 --> 00:02:54,059
I'll wait until Ha Na opens up.

52
00:02:54,698 --> 00:02:55,798
Come in.

53
00:02:56,798 --> 00:02:58,928
- Reverend Mother, Ha Na is here. - Yes.

54
00:03:01,999 --> 00:03:04,268
Hey. You should meet them.

55
00:03:04,569 --> 00:03:07,678
These are your dad's friends, Ha Na.

56
00:03:08,208 --> 00:03:10,809
- My dad's friends? - Yes.

57
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:13,319
Hello.

58
00:03:13,819 --> 00:03:16,178
You look just like your dad.

59
00:03:16,548 --> 00:03:19,119
Yes, I see her resemblance to Su Hwan.

60
00:03:22,819 --> 00:03:25,858
Everything burned down when she was seven years old,

61
00:03:25,988 --> 00:03:28,499
so she had nothing on her file when she came.

62
00:03:28,599 --> 00:03:31,268
She doesn't know what her father looks like.

63
00:03:31,499 --> 00:03:34,069
I probably have photos of your dad.

64
00:03:34,539 --> 00:03:37,208
But they are all from our childhood.

65
00:03:37,439 --> 00:03:40,309
But I still want to see Dad's pictures.

66
00:03:40,539 --> 00:03:43,379
You should visit us sometime. We'll show you.

67
00:03:47,018 --> 00:03:50,789
This is a present to remember our first meeting.

68
00:03:50,948 --> 00:03:53,758
- "A present?" - Yes.

69
00:04:03,899 --> 00:04:06,029
This is where you two will stay.

70
00:04:06,998 --> 00:04:10,009
If she doesn't know something, you can tell her, Ha Na.

71
00:04:10,308 --> 00:04:11,438
Okay.

72
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:14,308
Right, she doesn't know her name.

73
00:04:14,478 --> 00:04:17,509
Yes, we should give you a name.

74
00:04:18,048 --> 00:04:19,678
Is there a name you want to go by?

75
00:04:25,449 --> 00:04:28,589
You're close to Ha Na, so how does Du Na sound?

76
00:04:29,488 --> 00:04:31,789
- "Du Na?" - Du Na.

77
00:04:32,959 --> 00:04:34,159
Hey, Ha Na.

78
00:04:34,829 --> 00:04:36,829
So, what's her last name?

79
00:04:37,329 --> 00:04:40,099
Why don't you be a Lee, just like Ha Na?

80
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,368
Lee Du Na.

81
00:04:41,938 --> 00:04:43,938
You can live as Lee Du Na...

82
00:04:44,168 --> 00:04:46,139
until your memories come back.

83
00:04:48,238 --> 00:04:51,248
Lee Ha Na and Lee Du Na,

84
00:04:51,248 --> 00:04:53,519
you two must get along like real sisters.

85
00:04:53,618 --> 00:04:54,818
- "Sisters?" - "Sisters?"

86
00:04:54,949 --> 00:04:56,048
Yes.

87
00:04:57,149 --> 00:04:59,389
Then, I'll see you at dinner.

88
00:04:59,389 --> 00:05:00,519
- Yes. - Yes.

89
00:05:04,889 --> 00:05:07,259
- You really don't remember a thing? - No.

90
00:05:08,599 --> 00:05:09,759
What's this?

91
00:05:10,228 --> 00:05:11,899
My dad's friend gave it to me.

92
00:05:21,139 --> 00:05:22,909
- How does it look? - It's pretty.

93
00:05:34,418 --> 00:05:36,358
At this rate, I may end up losing Se Young, too.

94
00:05:38,228 --> 00:05:39,389
No.

95
00:05:40,128 --> 00:05:42,498
- It wasn't my fault. - Se Young.

96
00:05:42,728 --> 00:05:44,969
No. Stop it.

97
00:05:45,498 --> 00:05:48,139
Go away. Don't come!

98
00:05:50,168 --> 00:05:51,238
What's wrong?

99
00:05:51,969 --> 00:05:53,378
Did you have a nightmare?

100
00:05:53,579 --> 00:05:57,009
Mommy, what about Yu Jin?

101
00:05:58,209 --> 00:06:00,079
Did you dream about Yu Jin?

102
00:06:00,149 --> 00:06:02,978
Yu Jin came home and told the truth.

103
00:06:04,019 --> 00:06:05,418
She said it was my fault.

104
00:06:05,719 --> 00:06:07,358
It was just a dream.

105
00:06:08,118 --> 00:06:09,488
Nothing happened.

106
00:06:09,589 --> 00:06:11,228
She said it was all my fault.

107
00:06:12,089 --> 00:06:14,829
She said everything happened because I hated her.

108
00:06:16,969 --> 00:06:20,568
What if she comes back and says everything is my fault?

109
00:06:22,099 --> 00:06:23,269
It wasn't your fault.

110
00:06:23,839 --> 00:06:25,469
I told you to believe me.

111
00:06:27,378 --> 00:06:30,349
You were in the restroom.

112
00:06:30,548 --> 00:06:32,678
Yu Jin got on the boat alone during that time.

113
00:06:32,678 --> 00:06:34,079
You didn't see anything.

114
00:06:34,548 --> 00:06:35,649
And...

115
00:06:37,118 --> 00:06:40,159
Yu Jin won't come back.

116
00:06:41,318 --> 00:06:43,389
- Really? - Believe me.

117
00:06:45,058 --> 00:06:46,259
I'm scared.

118
00:06:49,659 --> 00:06:50,829
It's okay.

119
00:06:52,269 --> 00:06:53,798
Nothing will happen.

120
00:06:56,438 --> 00:06:59,068
You have me. You have nothing to worry about.

121
00:07:06,978 --> 00:07:08,519
It's a bug! What am I going to do?

122
00:07:09,918 --> 00:07:11,048
Wait a moment.

123
00:07:20,029 --> 00:07:21,128
I got it!

124
00:07:22,058 --> 00:07:23,928
You're really brave.

125
00:07:24,428 --> 00:07:25,769
- Me? - Yes.

126
00:07:26,329 --> 00:07:27,438
You're cool.

127
00:07:32,608 --> 00:07:33,709
It's wriggling.

128
00:07:34,909 --> 00:07:36,039
What should we do?

129
00:07:36,709 --> 00:07:39,849
Let's tell the reverend mother that we'll keep this.

130
00:07:41,149 --> 00:07:42,878
You want to keep this?

131
00:07:43,719 --> 00:07:45,719
It's a tiny caterpillar right now,

132
00:07:46,048 --> 00:07:48,589
but it'll be beautiful once it becomes a butterfly.

133
00:07:48,789 --> 00:07:50,589
This bug will turn into a butterfly?

134
00:07:51,029 --> 00:07:53,159
Yes, don't you want to see it?

135
00:07:53,759 --> 00:07:54,899
I do.

136
00:07:55,659 --> 00:07:58,298
Then, let's name it, too.

137
00:07:58,568 --> 00:07:59,668
Okay.

138
00:08:01,298 --> 00:08:03,368
You're Ha Na, and I'm Du Na, so...

139
00:08:03,769 --> 00:08:04,938
- Se Na? - Se Na?

140
00:08:08,709 --> 00:08:11,849
Then, you've ceased the ocean search?

141
00:08:11,849 --> 00:08:12,978
I'm sorry.

142
00:08:13,418 --> 00:08:14,748
Please continue!

143
00:08:14,748 --> 00:08:17,418
How are all these people unable to find just one child?

144
00:08:17,418 --> 00:08:18,889
A long time has passed.

145
00:08:19,488 --> 00:08:20,858
In most cases,

146
00:08:20,988 --> 00:08:22,458
the missing person wouldn't have made it.

147
00:08:22,918 --> 00:08:24,029
I'm sorry, Mr. Yoon.

148
00:08:24,389 --> 00:08:26,359
(The police for the people, staying true to the basics.)

149
00:08:31,568 --> 00:08:32,769
What are you talking about?

150
00:08:33,098 --> 00:08:34,938
How would you know if my daughter's dead?

151
00:08:35,838 --> 00:08:37,338
Which newspaper are you with?

152
00:08:37,639 --> 00:08:39,938
Do not dare to publish a single line like that.

153
00:08:39,938 --> 00:08:41,379
I'll end your career.

154
00:08:50,749 --> 00:08:51,848
Sung Ho.

155
00:08:55,789 --> 00:08:56,859
Where's Yu Jin?

156
00:08:57,359 --> 00:08:59,359
What about her? Why are you back home alone?

157
00:09:09,039 --> 00:09:10,239
Sung Ho!

158
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:18,649
What's wrong?

159
00:09:19,409 --> 00:09:20,578
Why are you here alone?

160
00:09:21,718 --> 00:09:23,149
I wrapped up everything.

161
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:25,389
"Wrapped up?" Wrap up what?

162
00:09:27,088 --> 00:09:28,389
Did you just say...

163
00:09:28,918 --> 00:09:30,859
you gave up on looking for her?

164
00:09:31,688 --> 00:09:33,058
There's no hope.

165
00:09:33,058 --> 00:09:34,499
What do you mean there's no hope?

166
00:09:34,499 --> 00:09:36,328
They haven't searched long enough to say that.

167
00:09:36,798 --> 00:09:38,999
And you just agreed and came home?

168
00:09:39,928 --> 00:09:42,639
How could you leave her there and turn around?

169
00:09:42,639 --> 00:09:44,168
How do you call yourself her dad?

170
00:09:47,678 --> 00:09:49,678
Tell them to resume the search.

171
00:09:50,348 --> 00:09:52,249
Tell them to find Yu Jin.

172
00:09:52,548 --> 00:09:54,678
Don't give up, Sung Ho.

173
00:09:55,078 --> 00:09:57,818
You're her dad. You can't give up on her.

174
00:09:57,889 --> 00:09:59,818
You just can't!

175
00:10:00,759 --> 00:10:02,088
Tell them to resume the search.

176
00:10:02,759 --> 00:10:05,159
Tell them to do it again.

177
00:10:08,058 --> 00:10:09,159
I'm sorry.

178
00:10:14,938 --> 00:10:16,399
It's all your fault.

179
00:10:17,369 --> 00:10:19,308
I tried so hard to stop you from going.

180
00:10:19,668 --> 00:10:21,879
We wouldn't have lost her if you had listened to me.

181
00:10:22,609 --> 00:10:25,649
We lost her because you insisted on going.

182
00:10:29,318 --> 00:10:30,548
Bring my daughter back.

183
00:10:31,548 --> 00:10:35,159
Bring my daughter back! Yu Jin...

184
00:10:39,489 --> 00:10:40,899
Yu Jin...

185
00:11:04,048 --> 00:11:05,418
How can you drink right now?

186
00:11:07,058 --> 00:11:10,218
I won't forgive you unless you bring Yu Jin home.

187
00:11:11,159 --> 00:11:13,389
I'll curse you for the rest of your life.

188
00:11:34,578 --> 00:11:36,678
Sung Ho!

189
00:11:36,678 --> 00:11:37,818
Let go of me!

190
00:11:38,348 --> 00:11:41,019
I can picture that poor girl trembling all alone.

191
00:11:41,088 --> 00:11:43,558
Please calm down, Yeo Jin.

192
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:46,458
Even if you go there now, Sung Ho...

193
00:11:46,458 --> 00:11:47,899
He's no longer Yu Jin's dad.

194
00:11:48,229 --> 00:11:50,229
She's now my daughter. I'm going.

195
00:11:50,698 --> 00:11:52,499
I'll go and find her.

196
00:11:52,629 --> 00:11:54,999
- Goodness, no. - Let go of me.

197
00:11:54,999 --> 00:11:58,539
You won't be able to see her even if you go there.

198
00:12:00,109 --> 00:12:01,239
Shut up.

199
00:12:01,578 --> 00:12:03,338
You have no right to say that.

200
00:12:03,338 --> 00:12:04,379
She's my daughter.

201
00:12:04,379 --> 00:12:06,678
If she was alive, she'd come back to us.

202
00:12:07,149 --> 00:12:09,279
She'll come to us even if you don't go there.

203
00:12:09,379 --> 00:12:11,318
What is this utter nonsense?

204
00:12:12,088 --> 00:12:14,359
You should want to find that young girl...

205
00:12:14,359 --> 00:12:15,718
who's out there doing who knows what.

206
00:12:15,918 --> 00:12:17,958
You want to wait until she comes home?

207
00:12:18,359 --> 00:12:22,328
Do you expect me to wait for 10 or 20 years until I grow old?

208
00:12:26,029 --> 00:12:29,269
There's nothing you can do even if you go there.

209
00:12:29,369 --> 00:12:31,308
How do you know if there's nothing I can do?

210
00:12:31,308 --> 00:12:33,068
You gave up before trying.

211
00:12:34,039 --> 00:12:36,879
I can't sit around and wait like you're doing.

212
00:12:36,879 --> 00:12:38,048
So what if you can't wait?

213
00:12:40,208 --> 00:12:43,048
Waiting is the only thing we can do at this point.

214
00:12:43,519 --> 00:12:45,019
Do you want to cry and wail?

215
00:12:45,348 --> 00:12:46,918
Do you want to beg and plead?

216
00:12:47,818 --> 00:12:50,318
Do you want to do nothing but stare at the sea?

217
00:12:51,428 --> 00:12:52,958
Then grow exhausted in prayer?

218
00:12:54,999 --> 00:12:56,198
Do you want to do that?

219
00:12:58,698 --> 00:13:00,298
If so, go ahead.

220
00:13:14,848 --> 00:13:18,218
This is all your fault! It's your fault!

221
00:13:21,119 --> 00:13:24,688
Yu Jin...

222
00:13:27,529 --> 00:13:29,598
Goodness, Yeo Jin.

223
00:13:29,859 --> 00:13:32,468
You'll end up ill, too.

224
00:13:34,098 --> 00:13:36,499
Yu Jin...

225
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:42,708
Yu Jin...

226
00:13:42,708 --> 00:13:45,448
No, my poor Yu Jin...

227
00:13:52,019 --> 00:13:54,818
Why didn't you say you were asleep at the beach?

228
00:13:54,958 --> 00:13:56,958
I thought they'd think I was a thief.

229
00:13:57,629 --> 00:13:59,889
Then, police officers would come and arrest me.

230
00:14:00,499 --> 00:14:01,899
I'm not a thief.

231
00:14:03,098 --> 00:14:04,529
So, it's a secret.

232
00:14:04,629 --> 00:14:06,598
Don't worry. I won't tell anyone.

233
00:14:09,239 --> 00:14:12,808
I saw in a drama that a character who lost their memories...

234
00:14:12,909 --> 00:14:15,979
got them back after bumping their head hard on the wall.

235
00:14:17,039 --> 00:14:18,409
- Really? - Yes.

236
00:14:25,688 --> 00:14:26,789
Like this.

237
00:14:29,489 --> 00:14:30,629
You should try, too.

238
00:14:32,289 --> 00:14:33,458
Do it harder.

239
00:14:33,458 --> 00:14:34,999
Your head needs that impact...

240
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:37,129
to make the cells come alive and bring the memories back.

241
00:14:39,269 --> 00:14:40,369
Ouch.

242
00:14:43,369 --> 00:14:45,568
I'll practice every single day starting tomorrow.

243
00:14:51,678 --> 00:14:52,979
Goodnight, Du Na.

244
00:14:53,479 --> 00:14:54,749
Goodnight, Ha Na.

245
00:15:02,989 --> 00:15:04,729
- Over here. - Hello.

246
00:15:04,729 --> 00:15:07,529
Hello, have you seen this girl?

247
00:15:07,759 --> 00:15:08,759
I don't think so.

248
00:15:08,759 --> 00:15:10,058
Can you take another look?

249
00:15:10,399 --> 00:15:12,529
And this is my phone number.

250
00:15:12,629 --> 00:15:14,639
Hello, please take a look at this.

251
00:15:15,139 --> 00:15:18,568
Have you seen her? She's about this tall.

252
00:15:20,009 --> 00:15:21,078
No.

253
