272
00:16:25,409 --> 00:16:28,808
I will always pray...

273
00:16:29,078 --> 00:16:32,779
for the good of your life as a priest.

274
00:16:33,279 --> 00:16:36,779
Let us recite The Disciples' Prayer.

275
00:16:37,818 --> 00:16:39,649
Father in the heavens,

276
00:16:39,918 --> 00:16:43,218
you have allowed us here today...

277
00:16:48,958 --> 00:16:50,229
Did you come here alone?

278
00:16:50,769 --> 00:16:52,668
No, I came with my dad.

279
00:16:52,668 --> 00:16:54,598
- Do you live around here? - No.

280
00:16:55,068 --> 00:16:56,199
In this children's home,

281
00:16:56,199 --> 00:16:57,709
- my dad's friend's... - Ouch.

282
00:16:58,209 --> 00:16:59,239
Are you okay?

283
00:17:03,709 --> 00:17:04,808
All done.

284
00:17:06,078 --> 00:17:08,719
I sewed it on tightly. It won't come off again.

285
00:17:10,219 --> 00:17:12,189
Where did you learn to do this?

286
00:17:13,419 --> 00:17:15,588
- I picked it up. - What?

287
00:17:17,989 --> 00:17:20,158
Hide well

288
00:17:20,158 --> 00:17:22,699
I can still see your hair

289
00:17:23,898 --> 00:17:24,999
I found you.

290
00:17:26,529 --> 00:17:30,439
What? I thought I heard someone.

291
00:17:52,088 --> 00:17:53,328
My gosh.

292
00:17:54,398 --> 00:17:59,029
I saw spring, summer, fall, and winter from this place.

293
00:17:59,328 --> 00:18:00,739
Which season was the best?

294
00:18:02,638 --> 00:18:03,739
All of them.

295
00:18:04,209 --> 00:18:05,368
Aren't you scared?

296
00:18:05,739 --> 00:18:08,439
"Scared?" It looks so awesome.

297
00:18:12,709 --> 00:18:13,808
Look.

298
00:18:19,919 --> 00:18:21,388
Ha Na, Ji Seok.

299
00:18:22,058 --> 00:18:23,219
- Sir. - Dad.

300
00:18:25,489 --> 00:18:26,658
You two were here together.

301
00:18:27,429 --> 00:18:28,628
You two should meet.

302
00:18:28,628 --> 00:18:30,999
She's Ha Na, the older girl I mentioned.

303
00:18:30,999 --> 00:18:32,499
He's my son, Ji Seok.

304
00:18:33,999 --> 00:18:35,669
Hi, my name is Lee Ha Na.

305
00:18:35,969 --> 00:18:38,308
Hi, my name is Goo Ji Seok.

306
00:18:50,949 --> 00:18:53,949
I'm sorry, Yu Jin.

307
00:18:55,959 --> 00:18:57,858
Daddy is so sorry.

308
00:19:00,328 --> 00:19:01,558
Just die instead.

309
00:19:01,898 --> 00:19:04,128
If you're going to drink the problem away, just die.

310
00:19:05,469 --> 00:19:07,638
Yu Jin won't come back if you sit here and drink.

311
00:19:07,638 --> 00:19:09,368
Drinking was the last thing I could do.

312
00:19:10,669 --> 00:19:13,039
I feel too stifled to go on.

313
00:19:13,108 --> 00:19:14,279
Do you want to go on?

314
00:19:16,138 --> 00:19:18,848
How can you want to go on after losing your child?

315
00:19:19,848 --> 00:19:22,749
If my death will bring Yu Jin back,

316
00:19:23,979 --> 00:19:25,848
I can die right here.

317
00:19:26,249 --> 00:19:27,348
Please...

318
00:19:30,719 --> 00:19:32,189
If your death can...

319
00:19:34,358 --> 00:19:36,029
bring Yu Jin back,

320
00:19:39,298 --> 00:19:40,368
then please...

321
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:43,739
die.

322
00:19:45,239 --> 00:19:47,138
I wouldn't have lost her...

323
00:19:47,908 --> 00:19:50,108
if you came with us.

324
00:19:51,548 --> 00:19:55,148
She begged you so much to come along.

325
00:19:57,719 --> 00:20:00,519
You turned her down for work.

326
00:20:02,658 --> 00:20:03,719
Are you...

327
00:20:05,289 --> 00:20:06,789
blaming me right now?

328
00:20:10,298 --> 00:20:13,969
Your priority isn't Yu Jin...

329
00:20:14,469 --> 00:20:15,868
or our family.

330
00:20:17,169 --> 00:20:19,338
It was always...

331
00:20:20,239 --> 00:20:21,408
your business...

332
00:20:22,638 --> 00:20:24,378
and money.

333
00:20:51,138 --> 00:20:53,408
Your shoulders are really hard for a woman.

334
00:20:54,108 --> 00:20:55,739
You should cut down on work...

335
00:20:56,108 --> 00:20:58,648
and spend more time with Yu Jin, too.

336
00:20:59,209 --> 00:21:01,618
As soon as I'm done with this project.

337
00:21:01,949 --> 00:21:03,449
Don't just say it.

338
00:21:03,949 --> 00:21:07,019
Yu Jin wants to go to an amusement park...

339
00:21:07,019 --> 00:21:08,719
and a swimming pool with you.

340
00:21:11,229 --> 00:21:12,689
Mommy, Daddy.

341
00:21:14,158 --> 00:21:16,398
- What's that? - Water for the night.

342
00:21:17,098 --> 00:21:19,898
- "Water for the night?" - I just watched a cartoon,

343
00:21:19,898 --> 00:21:21,969
and it said good daughters brought water for the night...

344
00:21:21,969 --> 00:21:23,169
to their parents in the past.

345
00:21:23,868 --> 00:21:26,169
So, Yu Jin, the good daughter,

346
00:21:26,308 --> 00:21:28,608
brought water for Mommy and Daddy?

347
00:21:28,608 --> 00:21:33,048
Yes, I'll bring you and Daddy this for the rest of my life.

348
00:21:33,749 --> 00:21:36,279
Are you not going to marry and live with us forever?

349
00:21:36,279 --> 00:21:39,318
Yes, I want to live with you and Mommy forever.

350
00:21:39,318 --> 00:21:42,618
- Gosh, is that so? - Daddy, stop!

351
00:21:45,259 --> 00:21:46,358
My gosh.

352
00:21:55,798 --> 00:21:58,868
He lost Yu Jin right before his eyes.

353
00:21:59,509 --> 00:22:01,709
It must be hard on him.

354
00:22:02,479 --> 00:22:05,808
He blames himself and drinks every single day.

355
00:22:06,509 --> 00:22:09,818
What if he considers the worst choice he can make?

356
00:22:10,048 --> 00:22:11,449
I've been feeling anxious.

357
00:22:12,818 --> 00:22:14,259
Please get my clothes.

358
00:22:15,118 --> 00:22:16,959
Are you going somewhere?

359
00:22:18,658 --> 00:22:19,959
I need to go to work.

360
00:22:20,929 --> 00:22:22,658
Will you be all right?

361
00:22:23,158 --> 00:22:24,398
I should be.

362
00:22:25,769 --> 00:22:28,368
I had private divers investigate the area,

363
00:22:28,838 --> 00:22:30,598
but she never showed up.

364
00:22:31,509 --> 00:22:32,868
She's not in the sea.

365
00:22:33,308 --> 00:22:34,979
She must be alive on land somewhere.

366
00:22:36,279 --> 00:22:40,009
I'll look everywhere people can go to and find her.

367
00:22:48,558 --> 00:22:49,719
I'm not going to school.

368
00:22:50,358 --> 00:22:53,858
My friends keep asking me why Yu Jin won't come to school.

369
00:22:53,989 --> 00:22:56,858
I told you to ignore them whenever they asked you.

370
00:23:00,398 --> 00:23:03,638
All right. I'll have another talk with your teacher.

371
00:23:04,669 --> 00:23:05,908
I want to go to a new school...

372
00:23:06,338 --> 00:23:08,039
where no one knows her.

373
00:23:11,209 --> 00:23:13,009
All right. You can transfer.

374
00:23:13,509 --> 00:23:14,679
This is hard on me, too.

375
00:23:14,679 --> 00:23:16,949
Are you sure she won't come back?

376
00:23:17,179 --> 00:23:18,449
How can she?

377
00:23:21,888 --> 00:23:24,959
So, when you go to your aunt's place,

378
00:23:25,229 --> 00:23:27,699
be a big girl and comfort your aunt and uncle.

379
00:23:29,398 --> 00:23:33,368
From now on, you need to do Yu Jin's part, too.

380
00:23:34,169 --> 00:23:36,169
No, I'm scared.

381
00:23:36,239 --> 00:23:37,638
Without her,

382
00:23:38,469 --> 00:23:40,509
you can become her.

383
00:23:41,779 --> 00:23:43,739
How can I become her?

384
00:23:43,739 --> 00:23:46,878
Does your aunt have any other children?

385
00:23:47,308 --> 00:23:49,179
Then, who's her closest relative?

386
00:23:50,648 --> 00:23:51,749
You.

387
00:23:53,519 --> 00:23:56,318
What will she do with all her fortune...

388
00:23:57,318 --> 00:24:00,088
in the bank and the business she does?

389
00:24:00,489 --> 00:24:01,929
She wouldn't pass it on to a stranger.

390
00:24:03,628 --> 00:24:06,898
Everything will be yours if you behave well.

391
00:24:07,499 --> 00:24:10,769
I'll make it happen.

392
00:24:11,068 --> 00:24:15,179
Will I really get everything that belongs to Yu Jin?

393
00:24:15,179 --> 00:24:18,048
Only if you do as I say.

394
00:24:22,318 --> 00:24:23,479
Ha Na.

395
00:24:25,818 --> 00:24:27,818
Se Na is gone.

396
00:24:27,959 --> 00:24:29,088
What?

397
00:24:29,689 --> 00:24:32,858
I came to feed it, but it was gone.

398
00:24:33,229 --> 00:24:34,358
I can't see it.

399
00:24:36,029 --> 00:24:38,199
You're right. Where did it go?

400
00:24:38,368 --> 00:24:42,239
I must've left it open for too long while I cleaned it up yesterday.

401
00:24:42,368 --> 00:24:43,539
What are we going to do?

402
00:24:44,469 --> 00:24:46,739
I wanted to see it turn into a butterfly.

403
00:24:46,969 --> 00:24:49,209
Did it become one already and fly away?

404
00:24:50,578 --> 00:24:51,679
Girls.

405
00:24:54,419 --> 00:24:56,679
What's wrong? Is something going on?

406
00:24:56,679 --> 00:24:59,419
Reverend Mother, Se Na is gone.

407
00:25:00,249 --> 00:25:02,019
What happened?

408
00:25:07,489 --> 00:25:08,828
Se Na is here.

409
00:25:08,999 --> 00:25:10,128
- Where? - Where?

410
00:25:10,529 --> 00:25:11,628
Right here.

411
00:25:12,529 --> 00:25:14,699
Se Na turned into a pupa.

412
00:25:16,199 --> 00:25:17,499
- A pupa? - A pupa?

413
00:25:17,808 --> 00:25:20,769
Well, for a caterpillar to turn into a butterfly,

414
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:22,509
it has to spend time as a pupa.

415
00:25:22,908 --> 00:25:25,848
It goes into that cocoon and makes its wings.

416
00:25:29,019 --> 00:25:33,088
Reverend Mother, then do people also go through a pupa period?

417
00:25:34,588 --> 00:25:36,989
Of course, everyone experiences such a period.

418
00:25:37,489 --> 00:25:39,729
You'll experience lonely, sad,

419
00:25:39,729 --> 00:25:41,628
and tough things in life,

420
00:25:42,128 --> 00:25:44,769
but you two will be so beautiful...

421
00:25:44,769 --> 00:25:46,769
when you turn into butterflies after that.

422
00:25:47,199 --> 00:25:49,499
I'm already looking forward to it.

423
00:25:51,539 --> 00:25:54,368
Then, we need to become pupas before we turn into butterflies.

424
00:25:54,368 --> 00:25:55,739
Gosh, pupas.

425
00:25:58,878 --> 00:26:00,949
Girls, let's take a look.

426
00:26:01,249 --> 00:26:03,749
Se Na looks very healthy.

427
00:26:07,519 --> 00:26:08,789
(MRI Scan Result)

428
00:26:10,289 --> 00:26:13,388
The result looks excellent, and so does the prognosis.

429
00:26:15,158 --> 00:26:16,259
My gosh.

430
00:26:17,628 --> 00:26:20,628
Good management is important after cardiac valve surgery,

431
00:26:20,798 --> 00:26:24,039
so he won't have any problems as long as you manage it well.

432
00:26:24,709 --> 00:26:26,169
Thank you, Doctor.

433
00:26:29,308 --> 00:26:32,348
It's all thanks to that lucky bracelet.

434
00:26:32,509 --> 00:26:34,949
You met the chairwoman and got the surgery...

435
00:26:34,949 --> 00:26:36,878
ever since you wore that.

436
00:26:37,449 --> 00:26:38,689
Do you still have it?

437
00:26:42,219 --> 00:26:43,318
Well...

438
00:26:44,888 --> 00:26:46,029
Where is it?

439
00:26:49,058 --> 00:26:50,429
You can have this.

440
00:26:51,169 --> 00:26:53,398
It won't be as good as family,

441
00:26:53,628 --> 00:26:55,669
but it'll keep you safe when you're in trouble.

442
00:26:56,499 --> 00:26:57,638
Stay strong.

443
00:26:58,209 --> 00:27:01,338
Why did you give it to someone? You should keep it on.

444
00:27:02,308 --> 00:27:03,608
Who did you give it to?

445
00:27:04,808 --> 00:27:05,979
A friend.

446
00:27:08,019 --> 00:27:09,118
All right.

447
00:27:11,348 --> 00:27:13,289
Let me close the door. Come here.

448
00:27:13,348 --> 00:27:14,658
Let me see your hat.

449
00:27:14,818 --> 00:27:16,419
It looks great on you.

450
00:27:18,088 --> 00:27:20,959
You can share this with your friends.

451
00:27:29,469 --> 00:27:31,169
Du Na, guys, I'm back.

452
00:27:31,638 --> 00:27:33,769
I got ice cream for everyone.

453
00:27:33,769 --> 00:27:34,878
- Really? - Really?

454
00:27:35,308 --> 00:27:38,449
He told me a lot about my dad.

455
00:27:38,449 --> 00:27:40,479
Ji Seok and Ji Eun are really nice, too.

456
00:27:42,148 --> 00:27:44,449
And the lady's stomach was already this big.

457
00:27:44,548 --> 00:27:45,848
She'll give birth to a baby very soon.

458
00:27:45,949 --> 00:27:48,318
This time, they won't give you up, right?

459
00:27:48,318 --> 00:27:49,888
They're your dad's friend.

460
00:27:51,789 --> 00:27:53,658
I also want to meet nice mommy and daddy.

461
00:27:54,189 --> 00:27:56,529
It'd be harder for us to get adopted if we grew any older, right?

462
00:27:58,969 --> 00:28:00,529
Let's go outside and play.

463
00:28:00,999 --> 00:28:02,638
- Okay. - Let's go.

464
00:28:10,078 --> 00:28:12,779
Du Na, why won't you eat the ice cream?

465
00:28:14,408 --> 00:28:18,249
I don't think my mommy will come for me.

466
00:28:18,719 --> 00:28:21,719
She must've abandoned me with the grandpa and left for good.

467
00:28:22,658 --> 00:28:26,529
Then, there's no way her friend will come and adopt me.

468
00:28:28,558 --> 00:28:30,398
I'll always be alone.

469
00:28:30,999 --> 00:28:32,398
You aren't alone.

470
00:28:32,729 --> 00:28:35,798
There's the reverend mother, me, and other friends.

471
00:28:35,969 --> 00:28:38,509
You'll have a new family soon.

472
00:28:38,669 --> 00:28:40,308
You're already my family.

473
00:28:40,838 --> 00:28:43,209
The reverend mother said we were sisters.

474
00:28:43,439 --> 00:28:45,408
We're very special sisters,

475
00:28:45,509 --> 00:28:47,949
so we'll be connected at heart even when we're apart.

476
00:28:48,078 --> 00:28:51,419
You will continue to be my sister even after you live...

477
00:28:51,618 --> 00:28:53,548
with Mr. Goo's family, right?

478
00:28:53,919 --> 00:28:55,219
Of course.

479
00:28:55,919 --> 00:28:58,558
It doesn't matter if we're apart or if anything happens.

480
00:28:58,558 --> 00:28:59,759
We'll always be family.

481
00:29:00,689 --> 00:29:03,429
Come to their place with me this Saturday.

482
00:29:03,898 --> 00:29:06,429
They both want to meet you.

483
00:29:06,429 --> 00:29:07,529
Okay.

484
00:29:11,908 --> 00:29:13,568
Hey, a butterfly.

485
00:29:14,068 --> 00:29:15,209
Really?

486
00:29:22,519 --> 00:29:24,689
- Se Na looks so pretty. - Se Na looks so pretty.

487
00:29:24,989 --> 00:29:27,489
The caterpillar turned into a butterfly, just as you said.

488
00:29:27,489 --> 00:29:31,088
That tiny caterpillar became such a beautiful butterfly.

489
00:29:31,489 --> 00:29:32,588
It's a wonder.

490
00:29:32,588 --> 00:29:34,128
Are we going to grow up like this?

491
00:29:34,729 --> 00:29:37,898
Do you think we're caterpillars or pupas?

492
00:29:37,898 --> 00:29:39,029
I don't know.

493
00:29:39,598 --> 00:29:42,338
Later, let's soar high together like butterflies.

494
00:29:42,669 --> 00:29:43,769
Okay.

495
00:29:45,408 --> 00:29:46,969
Se Na must want to fly, too.

496
00:29:47,469 --> 00:29:49,939
- Should we help her fly away? - When?

497
00:30:23,108 --> 00:30:27,348
(St. Paul's Home)

498
00:30:27,608 --> 00:30:28,749
We'll go, then.

499
00:30:29,749 --> 00:30:30,848
Say goodbye, Ha Na.

500
00:30:31,818 --> 00:30:33,088
Goodbye.

501
00:30:33,189 --> 00:30:34,818
- Goodbye. - Bye, Ha Na.

502
00:30:35,118 --> 00:30:36,259
Bye.

503
00:30:38,828 --> 00:30:39,929
Shall we?

504
00:30:49,039 --> 00:30:51,368
(St. Paul's Home)

505
00:31:01,818 --> 00:31:03,979
Let us go back inside.

506
00:31:08,959 --> 00:31:11,088
(St. Paul's Home)

507
00:31:11,888 --> 00:31:12,989
One moment.

508
00:31:29,308 --> 00:31:30,408
You can have this.

509
00:31:30,709 --> 00:31:32,908
But it's from those two.

510
00:31:33,179 --> 00:31:34,308
Are you sure?

511
00:31:34,509 --> 00:31:35,679
It's all right.

512
00:31:35,818 --> 00:31:37,749
It looks much better on you.

513
00:31:40,548 --> 00:31:43,618
This is a new hat, and you can have it.

514
00:31:45,429 --> 00:31:46,529
It's my present.

515
00:31:49,699 --> 00:31:51,598
Can I really have it?

516
00:31:55,138 --> 00:31:57,699
I think I've seen this hat before.

517
00:31:59,509 --> 00:32:00,939
Who's that girl?

518
00:32:11,318 --> 00:32:13,489
"That girl?" Do you remember something?

519
00:32:55,828 --> 00:32:57,858
(Cinderella Game)

520
00:32:57,929 --> 00:33:00,068
You don't have the right to stop searching for my daughter.

521
00:33:00,068 --> 00:33:02,199
You need to find Yu Jin, not anybody else!

522
00:33:02,368 --> 00:33:04,338
You can leave the chores up to us.

523
00:33:04,338 --> 00:33:07,108
All you have to do is play and do whatever you want.

524
00:33:07,108 --> 00:33:08,709
We're emigrating to America soon.

525
00:33:08,878 --> 00:33:12,108
They want to adopt you, Du Na.

526
00:33:12,108 --> 00:33:14,449
She thought her mother left her at her grandfather's home,

527
00:33:14,449 --> 00:33:15,979
so the police took her?

528
00:33:15,979 --> 00:33:18,489
Wait, what did I just see?

529
00:33:18,848 --> 00:33:20,749
A girl who looked like Yu Jin...

530
00:33:21,588 --> 00:33:22,689
What?
